Class CheckingAccount

java.lang.Object
CheckingAccount
All Implemented Interfaces:
Account
Direct Known Subclasses:
SavingAccount
public class CheckingAccount
extends java.lang.Object
implements Account
CheckingAccount.java implements the Account interface and contains the variables and methods associated with a checking account.
Author:
Rohan Murthy, Sridhar Varala

    • CheckingAccount

      public CheckingAccount​(int accountNumber, java.lang.String name, int cvv, java.lang.String expiryDate, java.lang.String type, java.lang.String password, double balance)
      The primary constructor for a checking account.
      Parameters:
      accountNumber - the account number associated with the account
      name - the username for the account
      cvv - the card verification value for the account
      expiryDate - the expiration date of the account
      type - the account type (chekcing or savings)
      password - the password for the account
      balance - the balance of the account

    • CheckingAccount

      public CheckingAccount​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String type, java.lang.String password, double balance)
      The secondary constructor for a checking account. This is the constructor normally called in CreateAccountGui.java when a new checking account is created.
      Parameters:
      name - username for the account
      type - the account type (chekcing or savings)
      password - the password for the account
      balance - the balance of the account
